contentrichtext.text: '''[[Zebulun]]''', was the sixth son of Jacob and Leah in the Hebrew Bible. '''Zebulon''', '''Zebulun''' or '''Zébulon''' may also refer to: *[[Tribe of Zebulun]], ancient Israelite tribe ;Given names *[[Zebulon Baird Vance]] (1830–1894), American Civil War hero and North Carolina Governor *[[Zebulon Brockway]] (1827–1920), American penologist *[[Zebulon Butler]] (1731–1795), American colonial soldier and leader *[[Zebulon Pike]] (1779–1813), American soldier, and eponym of counties in some states and Pikes Peak in Colorado *[[Zebulon Weaver]] (1872–1948), American politician *[[William Zebulon Foster]] (1881–1961), American labor organizer and Marxist politician ;Place names *[[Zebulon, Georgia]] *[[Zebulon, North Carolina]] *[[Zebulon Cafe Concert]] ;Other uses *[[Zébulon (band)]], music group from Quebec, Canada *"Zebulon", [[All Days Are Nights: Songs for Lulu|a song on the album ''All Days Are Nights: Songs for Lulu'']] by Rufus Wainwright *"Zebulon", a song on the album ''[[Tabula Rasa (Einstürzende Neubauten album)|Tabula Rasa]]'' by Einstürzende Neubauten *Zébulon, a [[Development of the TGV#Electric power|prototype TGV train]] *[[Zébulon (Paris Métro)]], former [[Paris Métro]] rolling stock *Zavulon or Zebulon, a [[Night Watch (Lukyanenko novel)#Dark Others|character in the novel ''Night Watch'']] and its sequels. ==See also== *[[Zeb (disambiguation)]] {{disambig}} [[Category:Human name disambiguation pages]]
